description.p:
(1) Silanes:
a) aqueous emulsions of an alkylalkoxysilane, e.g., DYNASYLAN® SIVO 850, (Evonik Industries, AG, Essen, Germany);
b) methyltrimethoxysilanes, e.g., DYNASYLAN® MTMS (Evonik);
c) methyltriethoxysilanes, e.g., DYNASYLAN® MTES (Evonik); and
d) monomeric alkylalkoxysilanes, e.g., Silquest™ A-137 (Momentive Performance Materials Inc., Columbus, Ohio), DYNASYLAN® OCTEO (Evonik), and DYNASYLAN® 9116;

(2) Siloxanes:
a) emulsions of modified polysiloxane resins, e.g., TEGO® Phobe 1650 (Evonik), and Shin Etsu X-51-1302M (Shin-Etsu Chemical, Co., Ltd., Otemachi, Japan);
b) solutions of amino functional polysiloxanes (“siloxane solutions”), e.g., TEGO® Phobe 1500 N (Evonik);
c) aqueous emulsions of silicone resins, e.g., CoatOSil DRI (Momentive); and
d) water-based emulsions of an amino functional siloxanes, e.g., CoatOSil 2059,

(3) Waxes:
a) natural waxes, including paraffinic wax emulsions, e.g., AQUACER® 497 (BYK USA, Inc., Austin, Tex.);
b) synthetic waxes, e.g., AQUACER® 530 (BYK USA), and AQUACER® 539;
c) wax dispersions, e.g., LUBA print 280/F (Munzing, Suddeutsche Emulsions-Chemie GmbH, Mannheim, Germany), LUBA print 2801w, LUBA print 434/F, LUBA print 445/w, and LUBA print 942; and
